{"comments":"Kelvin - color temperature of light sources.\n\nMeasured in degrees Kelvin from 1000 to 40000:\n- **1,800K**: Candlelight (warm orange)\n- **2,700K**: Tungsten/incandescent bulbs (warm white)\n- **3,000K**: Warm white LED\n- **4,000K**: Neutral white\n- **5,500K**: Daylight (reference white, \"D55\")\n- **6,500K**: Cool white (standard daylight, \"D65\")\n- **7,000K**: Overcast sky\n- **10,000K+**: Blue sky, deep shade\n\n## Physical Basis\n\nColor temperature describes the spectrum of light emitted by a blackbody\nradiator at that temperature. Lower temperatures produce warmer (redder)\nlight, higher temperatures produce cooler (bluer) light.\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- Light source definitions for glows, buttons, ambient lighting\n- White balance for photo/video rendering in LATTICE\n- Accurate color preview (\"how will this look under tungsten vs daylight?\")\n- Color grading (film look = warmer temps, clinical = cooler temps)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","Kelvin"],"Kelvin"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[81,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[81,1]},"title":"eqKelvin"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","Kelvin"],"Kelvin"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,40],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[82,1]},"title":"ordKelvin"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","Kelvin"],"Kelvin"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[85,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[84,1]},"title":"showKelvin"}],"comments":"Color temperature in Kelvin (1000-40000)\n\nRepresents the color of light emitted by a blackbody radiator at this\ntemperature. Used for lighting design, white balance, and color grading.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[79,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[79,1]},"title":"Kelvin"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a kelvin value, clamping to 1000-40000\n\nValues below 1000K (infrared) or above 40000K (UV) are clamped to valid range.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","Kelvin"],"Kelvin"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[94,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[94,1]},"title":"kelvin"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a kelvin value without clamping\n\nUse only when you know the value is valid (1000-40000).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","Kelvin"],"Kelvin"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[100,30],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/Kelvin.purs","start":[100,1]},"title":"unsafeKelvin"